{
  "exported_at": "2026-02-05",
  "sources": [
    {
      "id": 1,
      "source_title": "Mixed crop-livestock farming - What is mixed farming?",
      "source_org": "FAO",
      "publication_year": null,
      "source_type": "Report chapter",
      "source_url": "https://www.fao.org/3/Y0501E/y0501e03.htm",
      "accessed_at": "2026-02-04",
      "facts": [
        {
          "id": 1,
          "source_id": 1,
          "topic": "definition",
          "region": "Global",
          "fact_text": "Mixed farming exists in many forms shaped by external factors (weather, market prices, political stability, technological developments) and internal factors (soil characteristics, family composition, farmers' ingenuity).",
          "metric_value": null,
          "metric_unit": null,
          "metric_year": null
        },
        {
          "id": 2,
          "source_id": 1,
          "topic": "benefit",
          "region": "Global",
          "fact_text": "Farmers may choose mixed enterprises to save resources by interchanging them on-farm; this can enable wider crop rotations, reduce dependence on chemicals, align with nature-based preferences, and diversify risk.",
          "metric_value": null,
          "metric_unit": null,
          "metric_year": null
        },
        {
          "id": 3,
          "source_id": 1,
          "topic": "definition",
          "region": "Global",
          "fact_text": "Even pastoralists can practice mixed farming because their livelihoods depend on managing different feed resources and animal species.",
          "metric_value": null,
          "metric_unit": null,
          "metric_year": null
        },
        {
          "id": 4,
          "source_id": 1,
          "topic": "practice",
          "region": "Global",
          "fact_text": "Mixed farming can include mixed cropping (e.g., multiple crops or varieties with different life cycles on the same field) to use space efficiently and spread risks.",
          "metric_value": null,
          "metric_unit": null,
          "metric_year": null
        },
        {
          "id": 5,
          "source_id": 1,
          "topic": "classification",
          "region": "Global",
          "fact_text": "Three major mixed-farming categories are distinguished: on-farm vs between-farm mixing; mixing within crops and/or animal systems; and diversified vs integrated systems.",
          "metric_value": null,
          "metric_unit": null,
          "metric_year": null
        },
        {
          "id": 6,
          "source_id": 1,
          "topic": "classification",
          "region": "Global",
          "fact_text": "Modes of farming are described by land, labor and input availability: expansion agriculture (EXPAGR), low external input agriculture (LEIA), high external input agriculture (HEIA), and new conservation agriculture (NCA).",
          "metric_value": null,
          "metric_unit": null,
          "metric_year": null
        },
        {
          "id": 7,
          "source_id": 1,
          "topic": "classification",
          "region": "Global",
          "fact_text": "On-farm mixing refers to mixing on the same farm; between-farm mixing refers to exchanging resources between different farms.",
          "metric_value": null,
          "metric_unit": null,
          "metric_year": null
        },
        {
          "id": 8,
          "source_id": 1,
          "topic": "system_type",
          "region": "Global",
          "fact_text": "In integrated crop-livestock systems, crops provide fodder (grass, legumes, leys, weeds, residues) while animals provide draught and manure and serve as a savings account.",
          "metric_value": null,
          "metric_unit": null,
          "metric_year": null
        },
        {
          "id": 9,
          "source_id": 1,
          "topic": "principle",
          "region": "Global",
          "fact_text": "In mixed systems, maximizing the combined yield of components can be more important than maximizing the yield of any single component.",
          "metric_value": null,
          "metric_unit": null,
          "metric_year": null
        },
        {
          "id": 10,
          "source_id": 1,
          "topic": "challenge",
          "region": "Global",
          "fact_text": "Mixed farming can be poverty-induced; resource-poor farmers may rely on labor-intensive techniques and, with low purchasing power, may overexploit the environment.",
          "metric_value": null,
          "metric_unit": null,
          "metric_year": null
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": 2,
      "source_title": "Mixed crop-livestock farming - Integrating crops and livestock",
      "source_org": "FAO",
      "publication_year": null,
      "source_type": "Report chapter",
      "source_url": "https://www.fao.org/4/y0501e/y0501e07.htm",
      "accessed_at": "2026-02-04",
      "facts": [
        {
          "id": 11,
          "source_id": 2,
          "topic": "practice",
          "region": "Global",
          "fact_text": "Livestock products in mixed systems largely come from animals fed local resources (pasture, crop residues, fodder trees/shrubs) and village-industry by-products (oil extraction, grain milling, cane crushing).",
          "metric_value": null,
          "metric_unit": null,
          "metric_year": null
        },
        {
          "id": 12,
          "source_id": 2,
          "topic": "benefit",
          "region": "Global",
          "fact_text": "Recycling these resources saves money and reduces waste within the farming system, can create employment, and can improve soil texture and fertility while incentivizing multipurpose animals.",
          "metric_value": null,
          "metric_unit": null,
          "metric_year": null
        },
        {
          "id": 13,
          "source_id": 2,
          "topic": "benefit",
          "region": "Global",
          "fact_text": "Integrating crops and livestock intensifies organic matter and nutrient cycling; crop residues are the main on-farm source of organic matter and nutrients.",
          "metric_value": null,
          "metric_unit": null,
          "metric_year": null
        },
        {
          "id": 14,
          "source_id": 2,
          "topic": "benefit",
          "region": "Global",
          "fact_text": "Livestock act as capital assets for security and savings, provide cash income, and are part of nutrient flows; residue management is closely tied to animal feeding.",
          "metric_value": null,
          "metric_unit": null,
          "metric_year": null
        },
        {
          "id": 15,
          "source_id": 2,
          "topic": "benefit",
          "region": "Global",
          "fact_text": "Integration adds value to crop residues (especially legumes) through animal products and income.",
          "metric_value": null,
          "metric_unit": null,
          "metric_year": null
        },
        {
          "id": 16,
          "source_id": 2,
          "topic": "challenge",
          "region": "Global",
          "fact_text": "Long-term maintenance requires external nutrient inputs; as feed demand grows, cropland per capita shrinks, and crop yields decline, integration faces new constraints.",
          "metric_value": null,
          "metric_unit": null,
          "metric_year": null
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": 3,
      "source_title": "Mixed crop-livestock farming - Foreword",
      "source_org": "FAO",
      "publication_year": null,
      "source_type": "Report foreword",
      "source_url": "https://www.fao.org/4/y0501e/y0501e01.htm",
      "accessed_at": "2026-02-04",
      "facts": [
        {
          "id": 17,
          "source_id": 3,
          "topic": "practice",
          "region": "Global",
          "fact_text": "In mixed systems, livestock can use products not exploited by humans, such as kitchen waste, roadside/wasteland grasses, and crop residues.",
          "metric_value": null,
          "metric_unit": null,
          "metric_year": null
        },
        {
          "id": 18,
          "source_id": 3,
          "topic": "benefit",
          "region": "Global",
          "fact_text": "Animals provide multiple outputs (meat, eggs, milk, fiber, social status, income) and dung/urine that fertilize gardens, fields, and fish ponds.",
          "metric_value": null,
          "metric_unit": null,
          "metric_year": null
        },
        {
          "id": 19,
          "source_id": 3,
          "topic": "context",
          "region": "Global",
          "fact_text": "Traditional animal-keeping systems adapt to changes such as population pressure, fertilizer use, and consumption patterns; knowledge exchange helps develop useful technologies.",
          "metric_value": null,
          "metric_unit": null,
          "metric_year": null
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": 4,
      "source_title": "A classification of livestock production systems",
      "source_org": "FAO",
      "publication_year": null,
      "source_type": "Technical article",
      "source_url": "https://www.fao.org/4/v8180t/v8180t0y.htm",
      "accessed_at": "2026-02-04",
      "facts": [
        {
          "id": 20,
          "source_id": 4,
          "topic": "definition",
          "region": "Global",
          "fact_text": "Mixed-farming systems are livestock systems where more than 10% of dry matter feed comes from crop by-products or stubble, or more than 10% of total production value comes from non-livestock activities.",
          "metric_value": null,
          "metric_unit": null,
          "metric_year": null
        },
        {
          "id": 21,
          "source_id": 4,
          "topic": "classification",
          "region": "Global",
          "fact_text": "Rain-fed mixed-farming systems (MR) are mixed systems where more than 90% of non-livestock production value comes from rain-fed land use.",
          "metric_value": 90.0,
          "metric_unit": "percent threshold (more than)",
          "metric_year": null
        },
        {
          "id": 22,
          "source_id": 4,
          "topic": "classification",
          "region": "Global",
          "fact_text": "Irrigated mixed-farming systems (MI) are mixed systems where more than 10% of non-livestock production value comes from irrigated land use.",
          "metric_value": 10.0,
          "metric_unit": "percent threshold (more than)",
          "metric_year": null
        },
        {
          "id": 23,
          "source_id": 4,
          "topic": "classification",
          "region": "Global",
          "fact_text": "Landless monogastric systems rely on monogastric species (mainly chickens and pigs) fed from outside the farm, separating feed-use decisions from feed production and making nutrient flows open.",
          "metric_value": null,
          "metric_unit": null,
          "metric_year": null
        },
        {
          "id": 24,
          "source_id": 4,
          "topic": "statistic",
          "region": "Global",
          "fact_text": "Mixed-farming systems contribute the largest share of total meat production globally (53.9%).",
          "metric_value": 53.9,
          "metric_unit": "percent",
          "metric_year": null
        },
        {
          "id": 25,
          "source_id": 4,
          "topic": "statistic",
          "region": "Global",
          "fact_text": "More than 90% of global milk production is generated in mixed-farming systems.",
          "metric_value": 90.0,
          "metric_unit": "percent (more than)",
          "metric_year": null
        },
        {
          "id": 26,
          "source_id": 4,
          "topic": "statistic",
          "region": "Global",
          "fact_text": "Developed countries and Asia together contribute about 70% of total meat production from mixed-farming systems.",
          "metric_value": 70.0,
          "metric_unit": "percent (about)",
          "metric_year": null
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": 5,
      "source_title": "Chapter 1. Introduction (Mixed farming systems definition and scope)",
      "source_org": "FAO",
      "publication_year": null,
      "source_type": "Report chapter",
      "source_url": "https://www.fao.org/4/x5478e/x5478e02.htm",
      "accessed_at": "2026-02-04",
      "facts": [
        {
          "id": 27,
          "source_id": 5,
          "topic": "definition",
          "region": "Global",
          "fact_text": "Mixed farming systems exist where crop and livestock production occur in the same locality and ownership of crops/land and livestock is integrated.",
          "metric_value": null,
          "metric_unit": null,
          "metric_year": null
        },
        {
          "id": 28,
          "source_id": 5,
          "topic": "definition",
          "region": "Global",
          "fact_text": "Specialized livestock in the same locality may still be included as mixed systems if resource-sharing occurs, even with separate ownership.",
          "metric_value": null,
          "metric_unit": null,
          "metric_year": null
        },
        {
          "id": 29,
          "source_id": 5,
          "topic": "practice",
          "region": "Global",
          "fact_text": "Some mixed farming systems use farm trees for fodder.",
          "metric_value": null,
          "metric_unit": null,
          "metric_year": null
        },
        {
          "id": 30,
          "source_id": 5,
          "topic": "statistic",
          "region": "Sub-Saharan Africa (SAZ)",
          "fact_text": "In the semi-arid zone (SAZ), no smallholder farming systems were found lacking a livestock component.",
          "metric_value": null,
          "metric_unit": null,
          "metric_year": null
        },
        {
          "id": 31,
          "source_id": 5,
          "topic": "benefit",
          "region": "Sub-Saharan Africa (SAZ)",
          "fact_text": "Livestock provide investment capital and wealth creation for households, including for women.",
          "metric_value": null,
          "metric_unit": null,
          "metric_year": null
        },
        {
          "id": 32,
          "source_id": 5,
          "topic": "benefit",
          "region": "Sub-Saharan Africa (SAZ)",
          "fact_text": "Livestock provide recurrent income, manure for nutrient recycling, energy for traction/transport, and productive uses for farm residues.",
          "metric_value": null,
          "metric_unit": null,
          "metric_year": null
        },
        {
          "id": 33,
          "source_id": 5,
          "topic": "benefit",
          "region": "Sub-Saharan Africa (SAZ)",
          "fact_text": "Livestock offer a least-cost route to intensification through nutrient cycling, especially when inorganic fertilizers are costly.",
          "metric_value": null,
          "metric_unit": null,
          "metric_year": null
        },
        {
          "id": 34,
          "source_id": 5,
          "topic": "benefit",
          "region": "Sub-Saharan Africa (SAZ)",
          "fact_text": "Mixed farming can provide more productive use of scarce land, more defensible access to resources, a diversified and resilient household economy, and investment funds to rebuild livestock holdings.",
          "metric_value": null,
          "metric_unit": null,
          "metric_year": null
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": 6,
      "source_title": "Mixed-farming system; mixed farming (Glossary)",
      "source_org": "UN ESCWA (FAO source)",
      "publication_year": 1999,
      "source_type": "Glossary entry",
      "source_url": "https://www.unescwa.org/sd-glossary/mixed-farming-system-mixed-farming",
      "accessed_at": "2026-02-04",
      "facts": [
        {
          "id": 35,
          "source_id": 6,
          "topic": "definition",
          "region": "Global",
          "fact_text": "Mixed-farming systems involve crops, livestock and/or trees; livestock systems qualify when more than 10% of animal feed dry matter comes from crop by-products/stubble or more than 10% of total production value comes from non-livestock activities.",
          "metric_value": null,
          "metric_unit": null,
          "metric_year": null
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": 7,
      "source_title": "Integrated crop-livestock systems - a key to sustainable intensification in Africa",
      "source_org": "Tropical Grasslands-Forrajes Tropicales (CIAT)",
      "publication_year": 2013,
      "source_type": "Journal article",
      "source_url": "https://www.tropicalgrasslands.info/index.php/tgft/article/view/87",
      "accessed_at": "2026-02-04",
      "facts": [
        {
          "id": 36,
          "source_id": 7,
          "topic": "statistic",
          "region": "Global",
          "fact_text": "Mixed crop-livestock systems provide livelihoods for about one billion people.",
          "metric_value": 1.0,
          "metric_unit": "billion people (about)",
          "metric_year": null
        },
        {
          "id": 37,
          "source_id": 7,
          "topic": "statistic",
          "region": "Global",
          "fact_text": "Mixed crop-livestock systems produce about half of the world's cereal.",
          "metric_value": 50.0,
          "metric_unit": "percent (about)",
          "metric_year": null
        },
        {
          "id": 38,
          "source_id": 7,
          "topic": "statistic",
          "region": "Global",
          "fact_text": "Mixed crop-livestock systems produce around a third of the world's beef.",
          "metric_value": 33.0,
          "metric_unit": "percent (around)",
          "metric_year": null
        },
        {
          "id": 39,
          "source_id": 7,
          "topic": "statistic",
          "region": "Global",
          "fact_text": "Mixed crop-livestock systems produce around a third of the world's milk.",
          "metric_value": 33.0,
          "metric_unit": "percent (around)",
          "metric_year": null
        },
        {
          "id": 40,
          "source_id": 7,
          "topic": "driver",
          "region": "Africa",
          "fact_text": "Market orientation and strong, growing demand for food provide incentives for sustainable intensification of crop and livestock enterprises in smallholder mixed systems in Africa.",
          "metric_value": null,
          "metric_unit": null,
          "metric_year": null
        },
        {
          "id": 41,
          "source_id": 7,
          "topic": "benefit",
          "region": "Africa",
          "fact_text": "Better exploitation of the mutually reinforcing nature of crop and livestock systems can support positive, inclusive growth that is ecologically and economically sustainable.",
          "metric_value": null,
          "metric_unit": null,
          "metric_year": null
        },
        {
          "id": 42,
          "source_id": 7,
          "topic": "challenge",
          "region": "Africa",
          "fact_text": "Livestock intensification is often neglected relative to crops, even though livestock can raise the productivity of the entire farming system.",
          "metric_value": null,
          "metric_unit": null,
          "metric_year": null
        },
        {
          "id": 43,
          "source_id": 7,
          "topic": "benefit",
          "region": "Africa",
          "fact_text": "Intensifying crop production can benefit livestock and improve natural resource management via increased biomass availability.",
          "metric_value": null,
          "metric_unit": null,
          "metric_year": null
        },
        {
          "id": 44,
          "source_id": 7,
          "topic": "benefit",
          "region": "Africa",
          "fact_text": "Improved efficiency of livestock production means fewer greenhouse gases per unit of milk and more milk per unit of water.",
          "metric_value": null,
          "metric_unit": null,
          "metric_year": null
        },
        {
          "id": 45,
          "source_id": 7,
          "topic": "policy",
          "region": "Africa",
          "fact_text": "Greater investment in research for development is needed to identify win-win outcomes and enabling policies, technologies, and institutions for sustainable mixed crop-livestock systems.",
          "metric_value": null,
          "metric_unit": null,
          "metric_year": null
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": 8,
